deck: US based distributor to 7 countries in the Indian sub-region (South Asian Association for Regional Coorporation) in many languages. Among the distributed are characters owned by 5 companies, including DC, Marvel and Dark Horse.
description: Founded in 1997 Gotham distributed titles such as Superman, JLA, Spiderman, X-Men, Tarzan, Thundercats and even Flinstones and Powerpuff girls. They are probably best known for creating an Indian version of Spiderman dressed in a similar top and Indian pants who is closely but not completely based on Peter Parker. He has his own friends and family, including an Aunt Maya. It would later merge with Richard Branson's Virgin group to create Virgin Comics. Deepak Chopra and his son Gautam "Gotham" Chopra were among the founders of  this new company. One of their first new titles, Sadhu, a story about a soldier who was a monk, or a "sadhu" in his previous life, was to be made into a film with Nicholas cage in the lead, but was later cancelled or not well received.
name: Gotham Entertainment Group

deck: "The Home of Indian Superhero Comics"
description:
Raj comics is an Indian comics publishing company based in New Delhi. Also known as "The Home of Indian Superhero Comics", Raj comics is one of India's most popular comic publishers, and has a strong and a cult fan base.

It was established in 1986 by RajKumar Gupta. His sons Sanjay Gupta, Manish Gupta and Manoj Gupta became the next mentors of Raj Comics. Currently Manoj Gupta is the President, Manish Gupta is the CEO ,while Sanjay Gupta is the editor/creative head. Most of the companies famous characters have been created by him. Raj comics focuses mainly on superhero centric comic books.

Over the years Raj comics has come up with many famous characters including Nagraj,Super Commando Dhruv, Doga, Bheriya, Bankelal e.t.c. Apart from superhero based action comics,Raj comics also publishes light comedy and humor based comics in which characters like Bankelal, Gamraj, Fighter Toads are popular. Apart from these, Raj comics also publishes Thrill Horror Suspense series,3d comics, kids comics. They also publish knowledge books, Indian mythological and historical figures biographies, fable stories as well as learning books. Raj comics are published mainly in Hindi,but lately they have started publishing comics in English as well as in Indian regional languages.
name: Raj Comics

deck: Golfing / McCombs
description:
Golfing / McCombs was a minor publisher that produced, at least as far as I have been able to find, only one comic.

Crown Comics, which started in 1945 and ran to 19 issues.

While obscure the comic is notable for one of the first horror stories to appear in comics, a version of Poe’s The Oblong Box in Crown # 1, and one of the first black lead characters in a comic. Some of regular characters in Crown were Voodah, Clue Kelly, Ace of the Newsreels, and Magic Mickey.

Also, while their impact on comics was brief, ending in 1946, they had a much greater one in the fifties as the publisher of Seduction of the Innocent by Dr. Frederic Wertham.

They had no logo.
name: Golfing / McCombs
